entries.meaning: Resembling or characteristic of the herb thyme; having the aroma or flavour of thyme.
examples: All of us have read, no doubt, of the honey of Mount Hybla, of which the thymey flavour has been so much extolled by the ancient poets  […]

entries.meaning: Covered with or abounding in thyme.
examples: What time the mighty moon was gathering light
Love paced the thymy plots of Paradise,
And all about him roll'd his lustrous eyes;
